font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">, including healthy metabolism, muscle contraction and relaxation, glucose utilization, normal neurological function, and the release of neurotransmitters.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Magnesium’s many benefits include:</strong></span></p></div></div><div data-label="Icon List" data-key="icon-list" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1658631513106" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-iconlist" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1658631513106"><div class="module gf_module-left gf_module-left-lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs "><ul class="gf_icon-list"><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="1" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631513106-1" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631513106-1"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="1" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631513106-2" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631513106-2"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-182b65cb-7fff-a971-b211-61065a722119"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4455825/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Cardiovascular function</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: Healthy cardiovascular function and </span><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20353903/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">lipid metabolism</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">. It contributes to the regulation of vascular tone, heart rhythm, and platelet-activated thrombosis. It’s also required in enzymatic reactions in blood pressure regulation and cardiac excitability.</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="2" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631792011" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631792011"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="2" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631791922" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631791922"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7fd4d7af-7fff-12ac-2ac4-37f979d39716"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5926493/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Structural roles</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: It’s important for the structure of bones, teeth, proteins, many enzymes, and mitochondria. It is an essential cofactor in almost all enzymatic systems involved in </span><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11295157/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">DNA processing</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, including RNA and DNA synthesis.</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631801085" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631801085"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631801011" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631801011"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5a31112c-7fff-5ed2-45c8-445c8ca1b651"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1221685/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Muscle contraction</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: Magnesium stimulates calcium reuptake and is required for the active transport of calcium and potassium ions across cell membranes, essential for nerve impulse conduction, muscle contraction, and normal heart rhythm.</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="4" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631802412" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631802412"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="4" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631802460" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631802460"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-1f34b0fb-7fff-9404-5e26-6af6f4fcc45c"><a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6643/10/6/730" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Nerve function</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: Healthy nervous system function and </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3703169/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">sleep patterns</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> rely on magnesium. It’s also required for nerve transmission and neuromuscular conduction.</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="5" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631803694" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631803694"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="5" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631803760" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631803760"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-2a6995b5-7fff-ccd7-aeb6-936ddcc602d0"><a href="https://www.wjgnet.com/1948-9358/full/v6/i10/1152.htm" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Blood glucose control</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: Magnesium regulates insulin action, insulin-mediated glucose uptake, and vascular tone. And assists in </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5926493/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">daily energy production</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">.</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="6" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1658631804781" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631804781"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(54, 94, 153);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-arrow-circle-right"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="6" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1658631804776" class="element-wrap" data-id="1658631804776"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-4e643a32-7fff-fd81-c986-e9d7af75e41f"><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6524065/" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Maintenance of electrolyte balance</span></a><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> (the homeostasis of minerals within the cell).</span></span><br></p></div></div></div></li></ul></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" id="e-1654570798409" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1654570798409"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2>What Role Does Magnesium Play in Methylation?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658632044356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1658632044356"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left" data-gemlang="en"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">Methylation is an </span><a href="https://methyl-life.com/blogs/methylfolate-facts/mthfr-and-methylation" style="text-decoration:none;" class="" target=""><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">important biochemical process</span></a><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"> that “turns on” the biological switches that govern many bodily systems.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The methylation cycle requires one carbon atom and three hydrogen atoms (CH3) to be transferred from one component to another. CH3 is provided by SAMe (S-adenosylmethionine), the body’s primary methyl donor.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">To produce SAMe, however, the body requires methylfolate. A mutation on the MTHFR gene impairs the body’s ability to create methylfolate, which then impairs the methylation process, causing numerous dysfunctions and subsequent health conditions.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><a href="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q00266/entry" style="text-decoration:none;" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">Magnesium is a cofactor</span></a><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"> in methionine adenosyltransferase 1A (MAT1A), an enzyme that controls the production of SAMe.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">Magnesium is also required for the proper function of </span><a href="https://www.jle.com/fr/revues/mrh/e-docs/effect_of_a_natural_mineral_rich_water_on_catechol_o_methyltransferase_function_302731/article.phtml" style="text-decoration:none;" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">catechol-O-methyltransferase (COMT)</span></a><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">, the enzyme responsible for metabolizing catecholamines (neurohormones released in response to stress). Impaired activity has been linked to cardiovascular diseases, particularly hypertension.</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;"><br></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">Another critical enzyme with a high magnesium requirement is </span><a href="https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0304416516300071" style="text-decoration:none;" class="" target="_blank"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#1155cc;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">glutamine synthetase</span></a><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">, which drives glutathione synthesis.</span></p><p><span id="docs-internal-guid-8f502252-7fff-b55a-0e22-b54b26d194cd"></span><br class="Apple-interchange-newline"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" id="e-1658628508682" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1658628508682"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2>Identifying a Magnesium Deficiency</h2></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658632111257" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1658632111257" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-e